    "causal_summary": "The spec-kit generated metadata can fall out of sync with the docs it summarizes and nothing proves otherwise. There is no persisted proof that a stored causal_summary or description still matches the current docs because memory_save emits only an advisory and neither strict validation nor a dry-run backfill re-derives a folder to confirm. The description and causal_summary fields are also produced by two different extractors, so they apply different precedence over the same source doc and legitimately diverge. This phase adds checkGeneratedMetadataDrift that re-derives one folder and compares the generated fields ignoring volatile timestamps, persists source_doc_hashes as a cheap freshness key, and introduces one shared derivePacketSynopsis helper with explicit precedence and field-specific length limits used for both fields. Both behaviors ship behind a default-OFF flag and a grandfather report mode so existing folders that carry drifted or divergently-extracted text report rather than mass-fail, and the gate reports drift and never writes so it cannot churn the generated files the research exists to protect.",
